<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910913-0044</DOCNO><DOCID>910913-0044.</DOCID><HL>   Technology:   Computer Associates   Agrees to Acquisition   Of Pansophic Systems</HL><DATE>09/13/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B12</SO><CO>   CA PNS</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>SOFTWARE (SOF)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>ILLINOIS (IL)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   GARDEN CITY, N.Y. -- Computer Associates InternationalInc. entered into a definitive agreement to buy PansophicSystems Inc. for $290 million, or $16.15 a share, through atender offer.   Computer Associates said the offer, originally announcedSept. 3, is contingent on, among other things, the receipt ofenough shares to give the company a majority stake. Thecompany noted it must await the &quot;expiration or termination ofany applicable antitrust waiting period.&quot;</LP><TEXT>   Pansophic, based in Lisle, Ill., would be merged with oneof Computer Associates' subsidiaries. Both Pansophic andComputer Associates make software, primarily for mainframeand midsized computer systems. Pansophic, which had netincome of $20.6 million on $230.2 million in revenue in thefiscal year ended April 30, specializes in programs fordata-base management, logistics management and computer-aidedsoftware engineering.   Computer Associates, which earned $159.3 million on $1.35billion in revenue in the fiscal year ended March 31, focuseson utility, data-base and applications software.   In late New York Stock Exchange trading, Pansophic was up37.5 cents to $15.75, and Computer Associates was up 50 centsto $8.125.</TEXT></DOC>